node.text:
I was asked this question during a Live the other day.

It's a question I get asked a lot from new followers.

It's one of the most searched questions on google.

And for someone who is new in their nutritional journey, it's soo hard to know what to believe.
-
"Just tell me what to do and I'll do it."
-
But that only works for a short period of time.

When life gets in the way.

When the diet doesn't fit very well into your life.

When the diet makes you feel overly restricted.

So all I wanted to do with this post is highlight that the end goal should be to build the perfect diet for you.

You should be doing the "insert your name" diet.

That's the one that's going to yield lifelong success.

That's the one that's going to help you live your best life.

That's Nutritional Freedom.

The goal should be to build the perfect diet for you.

But to be able to do that, you must understand the nutritional principals that underly success.

What is your favorite Pop Tart Flavor of ALL Time?

Comment that flavor and tag your friend you’d smash this recipe with and you will be entered to win a copy of my Best Selling Recipe Book!
-
🚨Less than 175 Calorie Frosted Raspberry Protein Pop Tart Recipe!
-
✅ Macros for each Protein Pop Tart w/icing and sprinkles:
174 Cals, 28g Carbs, 2g Fat, 11g Protein!
-
✳️ Dough Ingredients (makes 6 Pop Tarts)
135g All Purpose flour
36g Powered PB
150g Plain Nonfat Greek Yogurt
10g Zero Cal Sweetener of your Choice
-
✳️ Filling:
100g Fresh Raspberries
-
✳️ Protein Frosting
30g Cake Pop @PEScience Select Protein
15g Powered Sugar
4g of Sugar Free/Fat Free White Chocolate Pudding Mix (optional)
2g Zero Cal Sweetener of your choice
-
✳️ Toppings:
20g Sprinkles
-
❇️ Directions 1️⃣ Add dry ingredients into a food processor, pulse to combine and add nonfat greek yogurt. Put food processor on low and run until dough is fully combined. Combine dough, place in a bowl and put in the freezer  for 15 mins. 2️⃣ Lightly mash raspberries with a fork until slightly chunky but not mushy.
3️⃣ Remove dough from freezer and split it in half. Place down the silicone rolling mat and sprinkle it with flour. Toss dough into the flour on the mat and roll out the dough into as big of a piece of dough as possible.
4️⃣ Cut out a pop tart size piece of dough. Then lay on the other non cut pieces as a mold to make sure each piece is the same size. Repeat this process. Any dough thats left over, combine together, roll back out. Repeat until you have 12 pop tart sized pieces of dough. 5️⃣ Lay one side pop tart dough down, add egg white wash outside edges, add raspberry filling to the center and then lay another piece of the pop tart dough on top. 6️⃣ Crimp down the edges of the pop tart using a fork and cut off the excess dough on the sides using a pizza cutter. Repeat this process for all six pop tarts.  7️⃣ Add to the air fryer for 3 min on 400 degrees. Flip over and cook for an additional 3 minutes. Repeat for all 6.
8️⃣ Now add the dry frosting ingredients to a bowl and add cold water 10ml at a time until thick frosting.
9️⃣ Frost the pop tarts, add sprinkles and enjoy!

Breakfast Bacon, Egg & Cheese English Muffin Sandwich!

Macros for the Whole Sandwich:
307 Cal, 29.5g Carbs, 9g Fat, 27g Protein!

Ingredients for 2 Sandwichs:
2 English Muffin (Mine had 25g Carbs each)
200g Egg Whites
1 Slice Turkey Bacon (I used Trader Joe’s version and those are big. So if you use a normal brand, then I suggest using 2 whole slice of turkey bacon aka one for each sandwich.)
2 Swiss Laughing Cow Cheese Wedges
40g Reduced Guilt Guac from Trader Joe’s. (Can sub mashed Avocado as well.) English Muffins Pizzas as Buns Cheeseburger!

Macros for the Whole Sandwich:
463 Cals, 34g Carbs, 15g Fat, 48g Protein!

Ingredients:
1 English Muffin (Mine had 25g Carbs)
100g Pasta Sauce
20g Light Shredded Mozzarella
6 Turkey Pepperonis
5oz 96/4 Lean Ground Beef
1 Slice Fat Free American Cheese
Sea Salt/Garlic Powder to Season Beef
1 Whole Egg

English Muffin Buffalo Chicken Sandwich!

Macros for each WHOLE Sandwich:
315 Cals, 29g Carbs, 7g Fat, 34g Protein!

Ingredients (makes 2 Sandwiches):
2 English Muffins (Mine had 25g Carbs each)
6oz (raw) Boneless Skinless Chicken Breast
1 Slice Fat Free American Cheese
Franks Red Hot Buffalo Sauce (I used Franks because it’s the most macro friendly)
1 Whole Egg

node.text: Some actionable steps you can take towards finding your purpose

🔥 Deli Fresh Crunch Wrap Supreme

✅Macros for the WHOLE Crunch Wrap (2 halves):
508 Cals, 47g Carbs, 17g Fat, 44g Protein!

✳️ Ingredients (makes 2 Crunch Wrap Supremes):
2 Large Flour Tortillas (mine had 34g carbs per)
2 Tostadas
10oz Boars Head Oven Roasted Turkey Breast
42g 2% Mexican Cheese
42g Avocado
Lettuce
Roasted Red Peppers
10g Sriracha

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ I recommend heating up your tortillas in the microwave for 10ish seconds to make it more pliable aka not going to rip when wrapping the crunch wrap.
2️⃣ Lay your tortilla flat and add your turkey and 2% mexican cheese to the middle. Then add your tostada. avocado, sriracha, roasted red peppers, and lettuce. Carefully wrap like a crunchwrap and repeat this process with your other crunchwrap.
3️⃣ Add to your air fryer and spray each with non stick butter cooking spray. Air fry on 400 Degrees F for 4-6 minutes or until golden. Flip at some point during once the top side of the crunchwrap is golden. Cook on that side until golden.
4️⃣ Then slice in half and enjoy!

🤤 No Bake OREO Protein Oatmeal Cookie Dough 

✅ Macros for the WHOLE Bowl:
456 Cals, 52g Carbs, 12g Fat, 39g Protein

✳️ Ingredients:
40g Old Fashioned or Quick Oats
30g Vegan Chocolate Protein Powder (I use my brand @flex_brands. “FDL” saves you 15%!)
12g Brownie Batter @ProteinCookieButter Powder (Vegan one!)
10g Black Cocoa Powder
3g Zero Cal Sweetener of your choice
200ml Unsweetened Vanilla Almond Milk
1.5 Reduced Fat OREOs

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Add all your ingredients (except almond milk and oreos) into a bowl and mix to avoid clumping.
2️⃣ Then slowly add in your almond milk and mix till all is combined. It will not be as thick as cookie dough but will be once you add it to the fridge to thicken up.
3️⃣ Mix in your crushed oreos and then add to the fridge for about an hour and then you are good to go!

*Highly recommend using a vegan protein here just because of how absorbent it is. This recipe is not meant to be vegan but the vegan proteins and cookie butters work super well together to get that thick cookie dough like consistency. If you do not have a vegan protein, I recommend using slightly less almond milk because a whey/casein blend or just a whey will absorb less liquid.

*If you do not have any cookie butter powder, I recommend just using more vegan protein powder to fill in the gap.

🔥 500 Cal Crunch Wrap Supreme

✅ Macros for the WHOLE Crunch Wrap (2 halves):
503 Cals, 45g Carbs, 19g Fat, 38g Protein

✳️ Ingredients (makes 2 Crunch Wrap Supremes):
2 Large Flour Tortillas (mine had 34g carbs per)
2 Tostadas
10oz 96/4 Lean Ground Beef
42g 2% Mexican Cheese
42g Avocado
Lettuce
Fresh Chopped Tomatoes
Yellow Mustard (for ground beef)
Sea Salt, Garlic Powder
10g Sriracha

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Preheat your stove top pan to a 6/10 heat. Add your ground beef to the pan and break up into crumbles with your spatula. Add your sea salt, garlic powder and yellow mustard. The yellow mustard is optional but you don’t even taste it and it’s a great way to keep the leaner ground beef from drying out. Cook till ground beef is browned and set to the side.
2️⃣ Now it’s time to put together the crunch wrap. I recommend heating up your tortillas in the microwave for 10ish seconds to make it more pliable aka not going to rip when wrapping the crunch wrap.
3️⃣ Lay your tortilla flat and add your crunch beef and 2% mexican cheese to the middle. Then add your tostada. avocado, sriracha, tomato, and lettuce. Carefully wrap like a crunchwrap and repeat this process with your other crunchwrap.
4️⃣ Add to your air fryer and spray each with non stick butter cooking spray. Air fry on 400 Degrees F for 4-6 minutes or until golden. Flip at some point during once the top side of the crunchwrap is golden. Cook on that side until golden.
5️⃣ Then slice in half and enjoy!

🍪 No Bake Protein Chocolate Cookie Dough Doughnuts

✅ Macros for each Cookie Dough Doughnut:
209 Cals, 17g Carbs, 5g Fat, 24g Protein

✳️ Ingredients:
45g Whey/Casein Blend Vanilla Protein Powder (I used @Flex_Brands. “FDL” saves you 15%)
45g PB Party @ProteinCookieButter Powder
25g Coconut Flour
4g Zero Cal Sweetener of your choice
115g Plain Non Fat Greek Yogurt
30g Mini Chocolate Chips

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Add all your ingredients (except mini chocolate chips) into your food processor and process until a dough ball is formed. Add to fridge till no longer sticky to the touch. Should take 30 minutes to an hour.
2️⃣ Once no longer stick to the touch, split the dough into 3 equal parts. Then roll with your hands one of the dough pieces into a thick rope. Then connect each ends of the dough into a donut shape and press together those ends. Repeat this process for your other 2 donuts.
3️⃣ Now take your mini chocolate chips and press into the outsides of the donuts.
4️⃣ Then it’s time to enjoy!

🌯 400 Cal Bacon, Egg & Cheese Breakfast Burrito

✅ Macros for each Burrito (2 halves):
428 Cals, 30g Carbs, 16g Fat, 42g Protein

✳️ Ingredients (makes 2 Burritos):
2 Josephs Lavash Breads
300g Egg Whites
1 Large Egg
4 Slices Center Cut Bacon
1.5oz Avocado
30g Roasted Red Peppers
42g 2% Mexican Cheese
Fresh Chopped Cilantro & Parsley
100g EASY Crispy Potato Recipe
20g Sriracha

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Preheat oven to 375 Degrees F. Line an oven safe pan with aluminum foil and evenly add your bacon to it without them touching. Make sure it’s a pan that has raised edges so not bacon grease can fall off the pan into your oven.
2️⃣ Add your bacon to the oven for 15-17 minutes or until your level of “doneness”. Add bacon to paper towels to help them crisp up.
3️⃣ While your bacon is cooking, make your eggs by preheating a stove top pan to a 5/10 heat. Add your egg whites and large egg. As it starts to cook, slowly move your eggs around with your spatula. Add your sea salt, black pepper and fresh chopped cilantro/parsley. Continue to scramble.
4️⃣ While your eggs are still a little runny, add your 2% mexican cheese and scramble. You want to make sure you don’t overcook your eggs. They are done when the excess moisture is gone from the pan but the eggs are still wet.
5️⃣ I want to preface when putting together the burrito that the lavash is really delicate so you will want to be quick with adding all your ingredients and then rolling it up. Why? Because the side getting all the ingredients added to it will start to get a tad bit wet/soggy from those ingredients and the longer your take, the more wet it will get thus making it hard to wrap without ripping it.
6️⃣ Add your avocado, then your roasted red peppers, bacon, eggs, potatoes and then sriracha. Fold over the outside edges of the lavash and then roll into a burrito. Please see video for what I mean.
7️⃣ Repeat this process for your other wrap. Add to your air fryer and spray tops with non stick butter spray. Air fry on 400 degrees F for 6-8 minutes flipping about 4-5 minutes in once you see the tops super golden. Once done, carefully slice in half and enjoy!

🔥 EASY Crispy Potatoes

✅ Macros for all the potatoes:
262 Cals, 54g Carbs, 3g Fat, 6g Protein!

*Added 3g fat to the macros for the cooking spray

✳️ Ingredients:
1 Medium Russet Potato (300g)
Non Stick Butter Cooking Spray
Sea Salt

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Slice up your russet potato long ways into about 4. Then slice across about 6 times to make into cubes. Add to a bowl of cold water to soak for 15-20 minutes.
2️⃣ Drain and pat potatoes dry. Spray with non stick butter cooking spray and add sea salt to them. Toss to combine.
3️⃣ Add to air fryer on 400 degrees F for 15-17 minutes. And that’s it! Enjoy!

Going to be throwing these potatoes into a breakfast burrito recipe here soon for you guys so be on the lookout for that soon 😁

🤤 No Bake Protein OREO Cookie Dough Doughnuts

✅ Macros for each Cookie Dough Doughnut:
204 Cals, 17g Carbs, 4g Fat, 25g Protein

❇️ Ingredients:
45g Whey/Casein Blend Chocolate Protein Powder (I used Flex Brands which JUST LAUNCHED THIS FLAVOR! “FDL” saves you 15%)
45g Brownie Batter @ProteinCookieButter Powder
25g Black Cocoa Powder
4g Zero Cal Sweetener of your choice
115g Plain Non Fat Greek Yogurt
2.5 Oreos

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Add all your ingredients (except OREOs) into your food processor and process until a dough ball is formed. Add to fridge till no longer sticky to the touch. Should take 30 minutes to an hour.
2️⃣ Once no longer stick to the touch, split the dough into 3 equal parts. Then roll with your hands one of the dough pieces into a thick rope. Then connect each ends of the dough into a donut shape and press together those ends. Repeat this process for your other 2 donuts.
3️⃣ Now take your crushed OREOs and press into the outsides of the donuts.
4️⃣ Then it’s time to enjoy!

🔥 383 Cal Breakfast Wraps!

✅ Macros per Wrap (2 halves):
383 Cals, 24g Carbs, 15g Fat, 38g Protein

✳️ Ingredients (Makes 2 Wraps):
2 Josephs Lavash Breads
300g Egg Whites
1 Large Egg
2 Laughing Cow Cheese Wedges
20g Green Onion
Pinch of Parsley
30g Roasted Red Peppers
42g 2% Shredded Colby Jack Cheese
56g Avocado
20g Sriracha

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Preheat stovetop pan to 5/10 heat. Add your egg whites, large egg, everything bagel seasoning, chopped green onion and diced parsley.
2️⃣ Scramble eggs until there is no excess liquid but they are not dry. Looking for wet eggs.
3️⃣ Lay your lavash bread down and on one end you’ll be adding all your ingredients. First, add your laughing cow cheese wedges and then spread it out. Then add your avocado slices, roasted red peppers, sriracha, eggs, and 2% colby jack cheese. Roll up your wrap super tight and repeat this process for your other wrap.
4️⃣ Preheat your air fryer on 360 degrees F. Add your wraps to your air fryer and spray the tops with non stick cooking spray. Air fry for 8 minutes, flipping after 5 minutes. Then slice up and enjoy!

🎃 Pumpkin Snickerdoodle Protein Cookies

🚨 We just restocked on Pumpkin Pie @ProteinCookieButter today so let’s do a giveaway! Let me know in the comments below your favorite pumpkin recipe that you love the most during #basicseason! Picking 3 of you guys to win a tub of the Pumpkin Pie @proteincookiebutter!

✅ Macros for each Cookie:
53 Cals, 5g Carbs, 1.5g Fat, 5g Protein

✳️ Ingredients (makes 18 Cookies):
60g Whey/Casein Blend Vanilla Protein Powder (@Flex_Brands “FDL” saves you 15%!)
40g Pumpkin Spice @ProteinCookieButter Powder (just restocked today!)
30g All Purpose Flour
20g Almond Flour
10g Coconut Flour
5g Zero Cal Sweetener of your choice
4g Baking Soda
Pinch of Sea Salt
100g Canned Pure Pumpkin
60g Sugar Free Pancake Syrup
2 Large Eggs
30g Granulated Sugar
3g Ground Cinnamon

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Preheat your oven to 350 Degrees F. Add all your dry ingredients into a bowl and mix to avoid clumping.
2️⃣ Add your wet ingredients and mix till you have a cookie dough like consistency. 
3️⃣ Line your oven safe pan with parchment paper and then use your cookie dough scooper to add the cookie dough balls across the parchment paper. I have a medium size cookie scooper. Remember this dough should make 18 cookies. Leave enough room to press these dough a bit before baking!
4️⃣ Dip your fingers into a little bit of water and then press the cookie dough balls into shape of medium size cookies like the chewy chips ahoy ones. Once all are pressed into shape, add your granulated sugar and cinnamon into a bowl and mix. Then sprinkle it on top of your cookies.
5️⃣ Add to the oven for EXACTLY 4 minutes. Once done, they might seem underbaked which is fine! Let them cool on the pan for 15 minutes or so to set. Make sure to not use a spatula or anything to take them off the parchment until they have set. If you lift them off their original spot, when they set, they will more than likely shrink more than we’d want. Once set, then it’s time to enjoy!

🤤 Hot Fudge Sundae Protein Pop Tarts Recipe!

✅ Macros per Protein Pop Tart: 194 Cals, 19g Carbs, 2.5g Fat, 24g Protein

✳️ Ingredients for Pop Tart Dough (makes 12 Pop Tarts):
70g All Purpose Flour
30g Whey/Casein Blend Vanilla Protein Powder (I use @Flex_Brands)
20g Brownie Batter @ProteinCookieButter Powder
20g Black Cocoa Powder
20g Almond Flour
8g Zero Cal Sweetener of your choice
140g Plain Non Fat Greek Yogurt

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Add all your ingredients into your food processor and process till a dough ball is formed. Add the dough to the fridge for 15 minutes to cool.
2️⃣ Time to roll out your pop tart dough. I use an XL silicone mat to help keep my kitchen clean and also it’s great at being non stick. Flour your surface and then add your dough. Split your dough in half and then roll out one of the halves of dough. If it starts to stick, add a little bit of flour to the dough.
3️⃣ Remember when rolling out this dough, you are making 6 pop tarts worth of dough so that means 12 rectangles about 4 in long and 3 in wide. What I did was roll out my dough and then cut out my first rectangle. Then I used that rectangle as a stencil for the rest of your rectangles. Repeat this process until you have all 12.
4️⃣ Lay down one piece of your dough and add about 25g of your protein frosting to the middle making sure you leave about an 1/2in on the edges. Brush some egg white wash on those edges around the frosting. Then take your top piece of dough and brush some egg white wash on the bottom edges to help seal the pop tart.
5️⃣ Add the top piece of dough and press down the edges. I dip my fingers in the egg white wash to help keep my fingers non stick. And when I say press down the edges, I mean really press them down! Gotta seal these well or they will open up when cooking. Crimp down the edges with a fork and then poke holes in the top with the fork as well. Repeat this process will all your pop tarts.
6️⃣ Preheat your air fryer on 360 degrees F. Make sure you do this step! Spray the bottom of your pop tarts with non stick cooking spray and add to your air fryer tray. Spray with non stick cooking spray. Air fry for 5 minutes.

Last step and Frosting/Icing👇🏻

🎉 Sugar Cookie Cheesecake Protein Cookies

✅ Macros for each Cookie:
66 Cals, 6g Carbs, 2g Fat, 6g Protein

✳️ Ingredients (makes 18 Cookies):
60g Whey/Casein Blend Vanilla Protein Powder (I use @Flex_Brands. Code “FDL” saves you 15%!)
40g Birthday Cake Batter (Whey Version) @ProteinCookieButter Powder
30g All Purpose Flour
20g Almond Flour
10g Coconut Flour
5g Zero Cal Sweetener of your choice
4g Baking Soda
Pinch of Sea Salt
100g Fat Free Cream Cheese (Room Temp)
60g Plain Non Fat Greek Yogurt
2 Large Eggs
45g Sprinkles

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Preheat your oven to 350 Degrees F. Add all your dry ingredients into a bowl (except sprinkles) and mix to avoid clumping.
2️⃣ Add your wet ingredients and mix till you have a cookie dough like consistency. Then add Then fold in your sprinkles
3️⃣ Line your oven safe pan with parchment paper and then use your cookie dough scooper to add the cookie dough balls across the parchment paper. I have a medium size cookie scooper. Remember this dough should make 18 cookies. Leave enough room to press these dough a bit before baking!
4️⃣ Dip your fingers into a little bit of water and then press the cookie dough balls into shape of medium size cookies like the chewy chips ahoy ones.
5️⃣ Add to the oven for EXACTLY 4 minutes. Once done, they might seem underbaked which is fine! Let them cool on the pan for 15 minutes or so to set. Make sure to not use a spatula or anything to take them off the parchment until they have set. If you lift them off their original spot, when they set, they will more than likely shrink more than we’d want. Once set, then it’s time to enjoy!

🔥 Crispy Waffle Hashbrowns as Buns Breakfast Sandwich

✅ Macros for each Egg White Patty:
81 Cals, 0g Carbs, 1g Fat, 18g Protein

✅ Macros for the WHOLE Breakfast Sandwich:
317 Cals, 34g Carbs, 9g Fat, 25g Protein

✳️ Ingredients for Egg White Patties:
150g Egg Whites Per Egg White Patty
7g 2% Colby Jack Cheese
Sea Salt & Black Pepper

✳️ Ingredients for the rest of the Sandwich:
2 Waffle Hashbrowns
½ Slice 2% Colby Jack Cheese
21g Avocado

❇️ Directions:
1️⃣ Line your 3.5in mini springform cheesecake pans with aluminum foil. Be careful to not rip the aluminum foil when doing this. Spray well with non stick cooking spray.
2️⃣ Add 150g egg whites, 7g 2% colby jack cheese and salt & pepper to each. Gently mix those ingredients together.
3️⃣ Add to your air fryer on 350 Degrees F for 15 Minutes. Once done, carefully remove from cheesecake pan and aluminum foil.
4️⃣ Now you can use these for meal prep later for sandwiches but now we are going to put together the breakfast sandwich. Take 2 of your waffle hashbrowns and add to your air fryer to reheat if these had been made prior. Add one of your egg white patties with ½ slice of 2% colby jack cheese on top to the air fryer. Air fry on 400 degrees F for 2-3 minutes.
5️⃣ Then put your sandwich together with avocado going on bottom hashbrown, then egg white patty and then the top waffle hashbrown. Then it’s time to enjoy!
